v1.0.0.description:
After almost an entire year I finally got around to updating this manual! Unfortunately it has some changes that aren't backwards compatible, so you'll have to update your yamls. Here's what changed:

* Wish Hunt and Life Mastery are no longer separate goals;
  * You can toggle them as required for goaling much like you could with main story and DLC;
* Story locations no longer split between chapters and intermissions;
  * Now all intermissions are grouped with their preceeding chapters;
* Story locations, both vanilla and DLC, can be toggled off;
  * Maybe you don't want the freebies from things you're forced to do anyway?
  * Maybe you found a way to use the manual with an existing save instead?
  * Whichever the case, it's an option now!
* You can toggle if progressive chapters get included in the multiworld pool rather than being fixed placements;
* Wish Hunt cap has been increased to 1000;
* Wish Hunt has an option of forcing lost wishes to be local;
* The Demi-Creator rank has been logically merged with the Creator rank;
* Fast progressive licenses have been removed;
* You can customize which licenses will be tracked and available;
  * Good for those solo life playthroughs;
  * Logic will account for unavailable lives as follows:
    * If it's a challenge or crafting location where the main life is included but the additional requirement life is not, the location will still be included;
      * You will be free to switch to the unavailable life for the purposes of requirements;
    * Otherwise, the location shouldn't show up;
* Life challenges and crafting were added as locations;
* Settings for other requests were altered slightly but function similarly to before;
* You can further customize which bliss bonuses will be available;
* Locations for "reach level 15 in X skills" have been removed;
* Other locations based on tracked bliss have been added or altered;
* You can now add level packs when including level up and skill level up locations;
  * Level packs introduce logical gating to reduce the odds of, for example, you having to increase your Longsword skill all the way up to level 15 because of a hinted item as if it were a sphere 1 location;
* Item restrictions were reworked to be based on progressive item rarity;
  * 0 star items are free, anything higher needs their star ranking in progressive items;
  * All forms of consumable items have been condensed into one category, consumables, rather than split among their various effects;
    * Easier to track this way, especially for items that did more than one thing;
* Shops and shop keys have been included;
* Red chest loot has been included;
  * Since red chests have drop tables per area, each entry on each table has been made a location;
  * Ability to exclude DLC chests, or just to exclude Ancient Tower ones;
* Cave passes have been included;
  * It's a prototype of map access randomization, similar to OSRS's AP and its chunk randomization;
  * Currently only restricts access to general caves, grottos and underground locations;
* A handful of DLC features now have an extra toggle to allow for more fine tuning;
  * For example, wanna include every bliss bonus in the pool but not deal with anything else DLC-wise? You can!
 
With the amount of changes I thought it warranted a bump in the major version. There's more I would have liked to add but given how long it's been since the last update, and also the fact I'm not sure how much longer I would have needed for those things, maybe it's time I at least upload something that's "working". Hopefully working, ha...

Some of the things I still want to do are:
* Include other types of chests (purple, invisible, master)
* Include an alternative to challenges or crafting locations in the form of tasks
  * Similar scope, collect X items or fight X enemies and the like;
* Add more goal requirements;
* Add template yamls for different setups, like different game modes;
* Look into other ways to allow a playthrough from an existing save;
* Look into other improvements;

v1.0.1.description:
No changes in the yaml but because of logical changes it's recommended to generate a new multiworld.

### Bug fixes:
* When DLC was included, some locations were listed under categories named C, D and L;
  * Definitely an oopsie from my part;
* Skill level up locations were not considering licenses as part of their requirements, only the skill level packs;

### Changes:
* Progressive chapters reintroduced as requirements for challenges, crafting recipes, levels and skill levels;
  * Acts as an additional layer of gating so you're at least on later chapters before logic expects you to grind levels;

